   microbial basal respiration was higher in 0-10, 10-20, 0-50 cm layers,
   while was lower in 20-50 cm layer under fly ash than that of coal gangue
   reconstructed mode. The lower Q(CO2) of fly ash mine soil suggested the
   lower maintenance energy requirement of the microbial community.
   Moreover, the contents of metals may possibly have negative implications
   for soil microbial and enzyme activities in reconstructed soil.}},
